{"title_page": "Ye (album)", "text_new": "{{good article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Ye\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Kanye West]]\n| cover        = Ye album cover.jpg\n| alt          = A view of the Teton mountain range with green text in the centre reading \"I hate being Bi-Polar its awesome\"\n| released     = June 1, 2018\n| recorded     = May 2018\n| studio       = West Lake Ranch, [[Jackson Hole|Jackson Hole, Wyoming]]\n| genre        = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length       = {{Duration|m=23|s=41}}\n| label        = \n* [[GOOD Music|GOOD]]\n* [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]\n| producer     = \n* [[Channel 7 (musician)|7 Aurelius]]\n* [[Benny Blanco]]\n* [[Francis and the Lights]]\n* [[Irv Gotti]]\n* Kanye West\n| prev_title   = [[The Life of Pablo]]\n| prev_year    = 2016\n| next_title   = [[Kids See Ghosts (album)|Kids See Ghosts]]\n| next_year    = 2018\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Ye\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Yikes (song)|Yikes]]\n | single1date = June 8, 2018\n | single2     = [[All Mine (Kanye West song)|All Mine]]\n | single2date = July 24, 2018\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Ye''''' ({{IPAc-en|j|e\u026a}}; stylized as '''''ye''''') is the eighth studio album by American rapper and producer [[Kanye West]]. It was released on June 1, 2018, through [[GOOD Music]] and distributed by [[Def Jam Recordings]]. Following controversy surrounding an interview with [[TMZ]], West re-recorded all the work on the album, with him completing it over the course of just two weeks at West Lake Ranch in [[Jackson Hole|Jackson Hole, Wyoming]]. \n\nGuest vocals from [[PartyNextDoor]], [[Ty Dolla Sign]], [[Kid Cudi]], [[Jeremih]], and [[070 Shake]], among others, are included on ''Ye''. West produced it with [[Mike Dean (record producer)|Mike Dean]], alongside numerous others. Succeeding the release of [[Pusha T]]'s ''[[Daytona (album)|Daytona]]'', the album is the second of five seven-track albums produced by West in what have been referred to as the \"Wyoming Sessions\", and set to be released weekly. It preceded the release of West's collaborative album with Kid Cudi, as [[Kids See Ghosts]], titled ''[[Kids See Ghosts (album)|Kids See Ghosts]]''. The latter's release was succeeded by that of [[Nas]]' ''[[Nasir (album)|Nasir]]'', and [[Teyana Taylor]]'s ''[[K.T.S.E.]]''. \n\n\"[[Yikes (song)|Yikes]]\" and \"[[All Mine (Kanye West song)|All Mine]]\" were released as singles in the summer of 2018 in support of ''Ye'', with a [[lyric video]] being released for the latter simultaneously with one for non-single \"[[Violent Crimes (song)|Violent Crimes]]\". Both of the singles attained top 20 positions on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], while the album received generally favorable reviews from [[Music journalism|music critics]]. The majority of them drew comparisons between the latter and West's previous works, while other critics had somewhat mixed feelings towards the lyrical content. It was named as one of the best albums of 2018 by multiple publications, including ''[[NME]]'' and ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''.\n\n''Ye'' became West's eighth consecutive album to debut at number one on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], tying him with [[Eminem]]'s record. It was also a chart topper in Australia, Canada, Estonia, Ireland and New Zealand, while reaching the top five in the Czech Republic, Denmark, Iceland, the Netherlands, Norway, Sweden, and the United Kingdom. The album has since been certified [[RIAA certification|gold]] and silver by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) and [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI), respectively.\n\n==Background and recording==\nOn February 24, 2016, West tweeted that his eighth studio album would be released during the summer of that year under the title of ''Turbo Grafx 16'', naming it after [[TurboGrafx-16|the video game console of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Byford|first=Sam|url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/2/27/11125294/kanye-west-new-album-turbografx-16|title=Kanye West says his new album is called Turbo Grafx 16 and coming this summer.|website=[[The Verge]]|date=February 27, 2016|accessdate=September 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143845/https://www.theverge.com/2016/2/27/11125294/kanye-west-new-album-turbografx-16|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> West associate Ibn Jasper posted a photo on [[Instagram]] showing West with longtime collaborators [[Mike Dean (record producer)|Mike Dean]], [[Plain Pat]], and [[Kid Cudi]] in a recording studio working on the album.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2016/02/29/kanye-west-kid-cudi-hit-the-studio-for-turbo-grafx-16/|title=Kanye West and Kid Cudi Hit the Studio for 'Turbo Grafx 16'|website=[[Rap-Up]]|date=February 29, 2016|access-date=July 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717185550/https://www.rap-up.com/2016/02/29/kanye-west-kid-cudi-hit-the-studio-for-turbo-grafx-16/|archive-date=July 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2016, [[Quavo]] posted an image on his Instagram of him in a studio with West, with \"''TURBO GRAFX 16''\" written on the wall behind them. A number of other artists were present in the image, including [[Lil Yachty]], [[Big Sean]], and [[Tyler, the Creator]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_uk/article/68937v/dang-this-photo-is-iconic|title=Important Questions Raised by This Photo of Kanye West, Lil Yachty, Quavo, Vic Mensa, Offset, Big Sean, and Tyler, the Creator|website=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|date=March 30, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421030437/https://noisey.vice.com/en_uk/article/68937v/dang-this-photo-is-iconic|archive-date=April 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The expected release of the album in the summer of 2016 was not met, while West began his [[Saint Pablo Tour]] in August that year, in support of his seventh studio album ''[[The Life of Pablo]]'' that had been released in February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/08/15/kanye-west-cruel-winter-yeezy-home-delayed-projects|title=7 cancelled, shelved, or delayed Kanye West projects|website=[[The Fader]]|date=August 15, 2018|accessdate=December 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191102123233/https://www.thefader.com/2018/08/15/kanye-west-cruel-winter-yeezy-home-delayed-projects|archive-date=November 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"tour\"/> The tour ended abruptly, with 22 out of 41 dates being cancelled, after West, on his [[Sacramento, California|Sacramento]] stop, embarked on a rant lasting roughly 20 minutes, ending the show.<ref name=\"tour\">{{cite news|last1=Savage|first1=Mark|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-38049884|title=Kanye West 'cancels entire Saint Pablo tour' following stage rant|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=November 21, 2016|accessdate=November 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161121190317/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-38049884|archive-date=November 21, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, news began to surface that West was working on his new album \"on top of a mountain in [[Wyoming]]\" in seclusion.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Davey|first1=Jacob|title=Kanye West Is Reportedly Busy Creating His Next Album\u2026 On a Mountain|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/2017/05/09/kanye-west-next-album/|website=[[Highsnobiety]]|date=May 9, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420202857/https://www.highsnobiety.com/2017/05/09/kanye-west-next-album/|archive-date=April 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Greer|first1=Carlos|url=https://pagesix.com/2017/05/20/kanye-hiding-out-in-wyoming-to-find-creative-groove/|title=Kanye hiding out in Wyoming to find 'creative groove'|publisher=[[Page Six]]|date=May 20, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420135509/https://pagesix.com/2017/05/20/kanye-hiding-out-in-wyoming-to-find-creative-groove/|archive-date=April 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2018, similar reports had emerged through various artists, including West himself, who was being spotted in [[Jackson Hole|Jackson Hole, Wyoming]], with a release date being expected for either 2018 or 2019 at the time.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nembhard|first1=Candice|title=Everything We Know So Far About Kanye West's New Album|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/kanye-west-new-album-details-release-date/|website=Highsnobiety|date=June 1, 2018|accessdate=December 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414143929/https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/kanye-west-new-album-details-release-date/|archive-date=April 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-wests-new-album-everything-we-know-news.46523.html|title=Kanye West's New Album: Everything We Know|last=Findlay|first=Mitch|date=March 26, 2018|website=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=June 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617015258/https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-wests-new-album-everything-we-know-news.46523.html|archive-date=June 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> A number of other artists were pictured or rumored, including Kid Cudi, [[Nas]], [[King Louie (rapper)|King Louie]], [[Pi'erre Bourne]], [[ASAP Bari]], [[Wheezy (record producer)|Wheezy]], [[The-Dream]], [[Travis Scott]] and [[The World Famous Tony Williams]].<ref>{{Cite news|last1=Strauss|first1=Matthew|last2=Yoo|first2=Noah|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/rumors-swirl-that-kanye-is-making-a-new-album-in-wyoming/|title=Rumors Swirl That Kanye Is Making a New Album in Wyoming|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=March 13, 2018|access-date=April 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421141433/https://pitchfork.com/news/rumors-swirl-that-kanye-is-making-a-new-album-in-wyoming/|archive-date=April 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Gardner|first1=Alex|url=https://pigeonsandplanes.com/news/2018/03/wyoming-kanye-west-travis-scott-the-dream/|title=A Breakdown of The Artists in Wyoming With Kanye West|website=[[Pigeons & Planes]]|date=March 13, 2018|access-date=April 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421163539/https://pigeonsandplanes.com/news/2018/03/wyoming-kanye-west-travis-scott-the-dream/|archive-date=April 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2018, West met with [[Rick Rubin]], who is the executive producer on West's previous two studio albums, ''[[Yeezus]]'' (2013) and ''The Life of Pablo''.<ref name=\"fu\">{{Cite news|last1=Fu|first1=Eddie|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/04/kanye-west-spotted-at-rick-rubins-recording-studio/|title=Kanye West spotted with Rick Rubin at Calabasas office|date=April 2, 2018|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|access-date=April 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421163324/https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/04/kanye-west-spotted-at-rick-rubins-recording-studio/|archive-date=April 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The meeting occurred at West's office in [[Calabasas, California|Calabasas]], following on from him recording in Wyoming, having bought a property in the latter named Monster Lake Ranch for recording and renamed it West Lake Ranch.<ref name=\"fu\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/23/style/kanye-west-cody-wyoming.html|title=Kanye, Out West|website=[[The New York Times]]|author=Bromwich, Jonah Engel|date=February 23, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224231846/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/23/style/kanye-west-cody-wyoming.html|archive-date=February 24, 2020}}</ref> That same month, West previewed the album for radio host [[Charlamagne tha God]].<ref>{{Cite news|last1=Penrose|first1=Nerisha|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8350853/kanye-west-previewed-new-album-charlamagne-tha-god|title=Kanye West Previewed His New Album For Charlamagne Tha God|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=April 19, 2018|access-date=April 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419235045/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8350853/kanye-west-previewed-new-album-charlamagne-tha-god|archive-date=April 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> West announced the album's planned release date of June 1, 2018 on April 19, simultaneously revealing it to include seven tracks.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sawyer|first1=Jonathan|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/kanye-west-kid-cudi-new-album-details-release-date/|title=Kanye West Announces Release Date for His & Kid Cudi's New Albums|website=Highsnobiety|date=April 19, 2018|accessdate=January 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414143937/https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/kanye-west-kid-cudi-new-album-details-release-date/|archive-date=April 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On April 28, 2018, West tweeted out a text conversation between him and Wes Lang.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Arcand|first1=Rob|title=Is 'Love Everyone' Really the Title of Kanye's New Album?|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/04/kanye-west-love-everyone-album-title/|magazine=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|accessdate=April 28, 2018|date=April 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429052209/https://www.spin.com/2018/04/kanye-west-love-everyone-album-title/|archive-date=April 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The text conversation included West showing the initial cover for the album, and an explanation of its concept, followed by him asking for help naming the album.<ref name=\"MTV\"/> Lang replied, \"''LOVE EVERYONE'',\" to which West replied \"I love that.\"<ref name=\"MTV\"/> The presented cover art showed plastic surgeon [[Jan Adams (surgeon)|Jan Adams]] who performed a [[liposuction]] and [[Mammaplasty|mammoplasty]] operation on West's mother, Donda West, which led to complications and eventually her death a day after.<ref name=\"MTV\">{{cite news|last1=Orzeck|first1=Kurt|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1579429/20080110/west_kanye.jhtml|title=Donda West, Kanye's Mother, Died of Heart Attack: Coroner's Report|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=January 10, 2008|accessdate=April 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080419083641/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1579429/20080110/west_kanye.jhtml|archive-date=April 19, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref> Within the texts, Kanye West explained that he wanted to \"forgive and stop hating,\" implying that West was ready to forgive the plastic surgeon for the situation regarding his mother's death.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Heller|first1=Corinne|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/930670/kanye-west-wants-to-forgive-doctor-who-performed-mom-s-final-surgery-with-an-album-tribute|title=Kanye West Wants to Forgive Doctor Who Performed Mom's Final Surgery...With an Album Tribute|website=[[E! News]]|date=April 28, 2018|access-date=September 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927083230/https://www.eonline.com/news/930670/kanye-west-wants-to-forgive-doctor-who-performed-mom-s-final-surgery-with-an-album-tribute|archive-date=September 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On April 30, Adams responded to the news of the cover in the form of an open letter, asking West to \"cease and desist using my photo or any image of me to promote your album or any of your work,\" while noting his willingness to sit down with West for a face to face conversation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kanye's Mom's Doctor to Yeezy: Love Deals With the Truth, I Didn't Kill Your Mom|url=https://theblast.com/kanye-west-dr-jan-adams-donda-west-letter/|publisher=The Blast|date=April 30, 2018|accessdate=April 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180501022800/https://theblast.com/kanye-west-dr-jan-adams-donda-west-letter/|archive-date=May 1, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> West responded to the letter on his Twitter saying, \"This is amazing. Thank you so much for this connection brother. I can't wait to sit with you and start healing.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/newsbeat-43960798|title=Kanye West: His mum's surgeon responds to album cover claims|publisher=BBC News|date=May 1, 2018|accessdate=November 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180501204734/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/newsbeat-43960798|archive-date=May 1, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nWest returned to Wyoming in May 2018 for the recording of then-upcoming albums, which were later referred to as the \"Wyoming Sessions\".<ref name=\"gq\"/><ref>{{Cite web|last=Cowen|first=Trace William|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/05/kanye-west-returns-to-wyoming-to-finish-new-albums|title=Kanye West Returns to Wyoming to Finish New Albums|website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=May 3, 2018|access-date=December 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728090013/https://www.complex.com/music/2018/05/kanye-west-returns-to-wyoming-to-finish-new-albums|archive-date=July 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Outside of his own albums, West also executive produced, produced, and provided guest vocals for all of the albums by other artists that came out of the \"Wyoming Sessions\", with him having announced taking on the role of producer beforehand.<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=Daytona|others=[[Pusha T]]|year=2018|type=booklet|publisher=[[GOOD Music]] and [[Def Jam Recordings]]|id=B0024894}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Indiana|first1=Jake|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/nas-nasir-production-credits/|title=Here Are the Full Production Credits for Nas' New Album 'Nasir'|website=Highsnobiety|date=June 18, 2018|accessdate=December 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806185915/https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/nas-nasir-production-credits/|archive-date=August 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-west-plays-zaddy-role-on-teyana-taylors-hurry-new-song.1979158.html|title=Kanye West Plays Zaddy Role on Teyana Taylor's \"Hurry\"|last=Ch|first=Devin|date=June 23, 2018|work=HotNewHipHop|access-date=December 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808081930/https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-west-plays-zaddy-role-on-teyana-taylors-hurry-new-song.1979158.html|archive-date=August 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Eustice|first=Kyle|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.46580/title.kanye-west-says-he-produced-nas-new-album-from-the-sunken-place#|title=Kanye West Says He Produced Nas' New Album From The Sunken Place|website=[[HipHopDX]]|date=April 22, 2018|accessdate=December 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180423065144/https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.46580/title.kanye-west-says-he-produced-nas-new-album-from-the-sunken-place|archive-date=April 23, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> American rapper [[Pusha T]] released his third studio album, ''[[Daytona (album)|Daytona]]'' on May 25, 2018, with the album standing as the first release of West's 2018 \"Wyoming Sessions\" recordings.<ref name=\"gq\">{{cite web |last1=Wolf |first1=Cam |title=The Best Song on Kanye and Kid Cudi's KIDS SEE GHOSTS Is\u2026 |url=https://www.gq.com/story/the-best-song-on-kanye-and-kid-cudis-kids-see-ghosts-is |work=[[GQ]] |accessdate=December 17, 2019 |date=June 8, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330193210/https://www.gq.com/story/the-best-song-on-kanye-and-kid-cudis-kids-see-ghosts-is |archive-date=March 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Abdul-Rashid |first1=Malik |title=''Daytona'' \u2013 Pusha T |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/daytona-mw0003180800 |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=December 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190506142909/https://www.allmusic.com/album/daytona-mw0003180800 |archive-date=May 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> West released ''Ye'' on June 1 as the second album of the \"Wyoming Sessions\".<ref name=\"gq\"/><ref name=\"AM\"/> Prior to referencing mental health on the album, West had mentioned it within his music in the past, especially on ''The Life of Pablo''.<ref name=\"health\"/> On June 8, 2018, a week after ''Ye'' had been released, [[Kids See Ghosts]], the [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] duo consisting of West and Kid Cudi, released their eponymous debut studio album ''[[Kids See Ghosts (album)|Kids See Ghosts]]''.<ref name=\"gq\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/kids-see-ghosts-mw0003183929|title=Kids See Ghosts \u2013 Kids See Ghosts|last=Yeung|first=Neil Z.|publisher=AllMusic|accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613184810/https://www.allmusic.com/album/kids-see-ghosts-mw0003183929|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> A sequel to ''Ye'' track \"[[Ghost Town (Kanye West song)|Ghost Town]]\", entitled \"[[Freeee (Ghost Town, Pt. 2)]]\", is included on the album, with the sequel featuring vocals from American singer [[Ty Dolla Sign]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Kornhaber |first=Spencer |title='Kids See Ghosts,' Kanye West, & the Wobbly Sound of Freedom |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/06/kanye-west-ghost-town-ye-kids-see-ghosts/562724/ |website=[[The Atlantic]] |accessdate=July 15, 2019 |date=June 14, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401153819/https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/06/kanye-west-ghost-town-ye-kids-see-ghosts/562724/ |archive-date=April 1, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> West revealed via [[Twitter]] that the former was originally slated for release on ''Kids See Ghosts''.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kim|first=Michelle|url=https://pitchfork.com/thepitch/5-takeaways-from-kanye-west-and-kid-cudis-new-album-kids-see-ghosts/|title=5 Takeaways from Kanye West and Kid Cudi's New Album, Kids See Ghosts|website=Pitchfork|date=June 8, 2018|access-date=June 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143655/https://pitchfork.com/thepitch/5-takeaways-from-kanye-west-and-kid-cudis-new-album-kids-see-ghosts/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On June 15, 2018, American rapper Nas released his eleventh studio album, ''[[Nasir (album)|Nasir]]'', which stood as the fourth album of the \"Wyoming Sessions\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kellman |first1=Andy |title=''Nasir'' \u2013 Nas |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/nasir-mw0003186198 |publisher=AllMusic |accessdate=August 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190428154422/https://www.allmusic.com/album/nasir-mw0003186198 |archive-date=April 28, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Helman |first1=Peter |title=Nas' New Album: Livestream The Queens Listening Party |url=https://www.stereogum.com/2001718/livestream-nas-queens-listening-party-for-new-album-nasir/video/ |work=[[Stereogum]] |date=June 14, 2018 |accessdate=August 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806185917/https://www.stereogum.com/2001718/livestream-nas-queens-listening-party-for-new-album-nasir/video/ |archive-date=August 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> American recording artist [[Teyana Taylor]] released her second studio album, ''[[K.T.S.E.]]'' on June 23 as the fifth and final album of the \"Wyoming Sessions\".<ref>{{cite web |title=''K.T.S.E.'' \u2013 Teyana Taylor |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/ktse-mw0003188128 |publisher=AllMusic |accessdate=August 8, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808081933/https://www.allmusic.com/album/ktse-mw0003188128 |archive-date=August 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/kanye-wyoming-albums-ultimate-playlist-2346377|title=Kanye and company's 'Wyoming albums' \u2013 the ultimate, brutally edited, best-of playlist|last=Britton|first=Luke Morgan|date=June 28, 2018|work=[[NME]]|access-date=August 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808081937/https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/kanye-wyoming-albums-ultimate-playlist-2346377|archive-date=August 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn an interview conducted during the listening party for ''Ye'', West stated that he \"redid the whole album after [[TMZ]],\" referring to a controversial interview with the tabloid news website in May 2018, during which he made controversial comments about slavery, and suggested that the entire album was re-recorded in a month.<ref name=\"redid\">{{cite news | url=https://www.rap-up.com/2018/06/03/kanye-west-redid-ye-album-after-tmz-interview/ | title=Kanye West Says He Redid Entire 'ye' Album After TMZ Interview | date=June 3, 2018 | website=Rap-Up | access-date=September 27, 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927083227/https://www.rap-up.com/2018/06/03/kanye-west-redid-ye-album-after-tmz-interview/ | archive-date=September 27, 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref> Referencing the recording process, West claimed that initially: \"Everything was going perfect. As soon as stuff stopped going so perfectly, I was like, 'I know what to do with this energy. I know exactly what to do with this.'\"<ref name=\"redid\"/> On June 4, 2018, West's wife [[Kim Kardashian]] reconfirmed this and revealed that two weeks were spent re-recording ''Ye''.<ref name=\"et\"/> Of her presence in the studio, Kardashian said: \"I left to go home for, like, two days and then I come back and it was a whole new album. It's fascinating to see the process.\"<ref name=\"et\">{{cite news | author=Tailor, Leena | url=https://www.etonline.com/kim-kardashian-reveals-how-she-reacted-to-kanye-west-exposing-their-marital-drama-on-ye-exclusive | title=Kim Kardashian Reveals How She Reacted to Kanye West Exposing Their Marital Drama on 'Ye' (Exclusive) | date=June 4, 2018 | website=[[Entertainment Tonight]] | access-date=September 27, 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927083228/https://www.etonline.com/kim-kardashian-reveals-how-she-reacted-to-kanye-west-exposing-their-marital-drama-on-ye-exclusive | archive-date=September 27, 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref> The following day, featured artist [[070 Shake]] said in an interview that the album was still being worked on up until the day before it came out.<ref name=\"Shake\">{{cite magazine|last1=Klinkenberg|first1=Brendan|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/070-shake-interview-ye-kanye-west-kid-cudi-ghost-town-w521108|title=How 070 Shake Stole the Show on Kanye West's New Album|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=June 5, 2018|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180608213308/https://www.rollingstone.com/070-shake-interview-ye-kanye-west-kid-cudi-ghost-town-w521108|archive-date=June 8, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She elaborated, revealing that West was \"very calm\" while completing recording sessions in a few hours.<ref name=\"Shake\"/> As well as 070 Shake, the album includes guest contributions from Ty Dolla Sign, [[Ant Clemons]], [[Jeremih]], Kid Cudi, [[Charlie Wilson (singer)|Charlie Wilson]], [[Caroline Shaw]] and [[Nicki Minaj]].<ref name=\"Tidal\"/> Though all of the other contributions are guest vocals, Nicki Minaj contributed a [[voicemail]].<ref name=\"Tidal\"/> ''Ye'' was updated on streaming services on November 8, 2018, with the uncredited sample of Kareem Lotfy's recording \"Fr3sh\" being removed from the track \"[[I Thought About Killing You]]\".<ref name=\"Lotfy\"/>\n\n==Music and composition==\n{{Listen\n| filename = KSG Ghost Town.ogg\n| pos = right\n| title = \"Ghost Town\"\n| description = Sample of the track \"[[Ghost Town (Kanye West song)|Ghost Town]]\", including West rapping unfinished thoughts in a dazed tone with the same verse melody as \"[[Runaway (Kanye West song)|Runaway]]\", and a refrain performed by [[Kid Cudi]].<ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/>}}\nWriting for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', Brendan Klinkenberg characterized ''Ye'' as a hip hop album, though viewed it as the opposite \"of a laser-focused statement album.\"<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/kanye-west-ye-pusha-t-daytona-short-albums-w521001|title=On 'Daytona' and 'Ye', Kanye West Proves the Strengths (and Limitations) of a Short Album|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=June 1, 2018|access-date=June 1, 2018|last=Klinkenberg|first=Brendan|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180602215505/https://www.rollingstone.com/kanye-west-ye-pusha-t-daytona-short-albums-w521001|archive-date=June 2, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Lindsay Zoladz of [[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] noted the album's rushed sound, describing it as what \"has a slapdash, unfinished quality about it, like a 10-page paper written in a shaky hand on the bumpy morning bus ride to school.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theringer.com/2018/6/2/17420710/kanye-west-ye-album-review-kid-cudi-070-shake-valee-nicki-minaj|title=Make 'Ye' Great Again: Kanye West's New Album Is Not Worth the Mental Gymnastics It Demands|publisher=[[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]]|date=June 3, 2018|access-date=September 27, 2019|last=Zoladz|first=Lindsay|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927083229/https://www.theringer.com/2018/6/2/17420710/kanye-west-ye-album-review-kid-cudi-070-shake-valee-nicki-minaj|archive-date=September 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> For ''[[The Line of Best Fit]]'', Ross Horton similarly stated that ''Ye'' \"just sounds like it hasn't been finished,\" specifically noting the track \"[[Wouldn't Leave]]\" as sounding unfinished.<ref name=\"line\"/> Douglas Greenwood from ''[[NME]]'' wrote that the album \"lacks the profundity of ''[[My Beautiful Dark Twisted Fantasy]]'' and the audacity of ''[[808s & Heartbreak|808s]]'' or ''Yeezus'',\" calling the sound \"succinct and easy to swallow.\"<ref name=\"NME\"/>\n\nSteven Hyden compared the composition of the tracks on ''Ye'' to West's previous works in [[Uproxx]], expressing the viewpoint that none of them stand out \"as a decisive break with what he's done before.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Hyden|first=Steven|url=https://uproxx.com/music/kanye-west-ye-review-career-overview-my-beautiful-dark-twisted-fantasy/|title=From 'Dark Fantasy' To 'Ye,' Kanye West's Decade-Long Slide From Greatness To Mediocrity|publisher=[[Uproxx]]|date=June 5, 2019|access-date=November 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190903095525/https://uproxx.com/music/kanye-west-ye-review-career-overview-my-beautiful-dark-twisted-fantasy/|archive-date=September 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Paul Bowler from ''uDiscoverMusic'' viewed the work on the album as taking influence from West's previous tracks, describing it as what \"marked a return to the dusty soul samples with which he had first made his name in the mid-00s.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Bowler|first=Paul|url=https://www.udiscovermusic.com/stories/yanye-west-ye-album/|title='ye': How Kanye West Turned A Controversy into A Response To Critics|website=uDiscoverMusic|date=June 1, 2019|access-date=October 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825041813/https://www.udiscovermusic.com/stories/yanye-west-ye-album/|archive-date=August 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Similarly, Clayton Purdom of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' claimed that the old West is present on ''Ye'' \"bringing plump, stirring soul samples.\"<ref name=\"AVClub\"/> He elaborated, writing that \"if you missed the new Kanye, there's plenty of abrasive, ''Yeezus''-style abstraction, too,\" and noted the inclusion of multitudes on the album.<ref name=\"AVClub\"/> Writing for ''[[The Observer]]'', [[Kitty Empire]] viewed the work as \"veering between sparse, hyper-modern styles and compositions which hark back to the soulful bent\" of West's early career.<ref name=\"Observer\"/> Lucy Jones of ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' noted certain works as being reminiscent of West's third studio album ''[[Graduation (album)|Graduation]]'' (2007), viewing the piano chords and [[Slick Rick]] sample on the track \"[[No Mistakes]]\" as \"old-school West,\" which she also pointed to certain vocals on \"Ghost Town\" as being.<ref name=\"Telegraph\"/>\n\n==Themes and lyrics==\n''Ye'' gives a look into the psyche of West, with the character of him being focused on.<ref name=\"AM\"/><ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/> The album includes references to West's mental health, with a large amount of it seeing him unravel his mind, and \"Ghost Town\" is specifically linked to the theme.<ref name=\"Guardian\"/> The theme contrasts ''The Life of Pablo''{{'}}s delving into the darker corners of fame and family, with ''Ye'' being more uncomfortable in comparison.<ref name=\"AM\"/> West's [[bipolar disorder]] and suicidal thoughts are mentioned on the album, which are in relation to the theme of mental health.<ref name=\"health\"/> ''Ye'' also includes West expressing his thoughts towards women.<ref name=\"Guardian\"/>\n\nThe album's opener, \"I Thought About Killing You\", sees West confess to thoughts of both suicide and homicide.<ref name=\"NME\"/> West delivers [[spoken word]] over a backing vocal within the opener for a couple of minutes until the beat changes and he switches to rapping.<ref name=\"Telegraph\"/> \"[[Yikes (song)|Yikes]]\" includes West referencing his experiences with [[psychedelic drug]]s, as well as his struggle with mental health.<ref name=\"various\"/> Within \"[[All Mine (Kanye West song)|All Mine]]\", West moves \"into more explicit territory\" and raps about having interest in multiple dating options.<ref name=\"NME\"/><ref name=\"Telegraph\"/> West uses \"Wouldn't Leave\" to reference his controversial comments about slavery, and his relationship with Kardashian.<ref name=\"Telegraph\"/> \"No Mistakes\" includes a series of self-righteous outbursts, coming from the perspective of a multi millionaire in West.<ref name=\"Observer\"/> The mind of West is presented as being in the process of unravelling within \"Ghost Town\", which is in reference to his mental health state.<ref name=\"Guardian\"/> West raps about fears towards fathering his daughter within \"[[Violent Crimes (song)|Violent Crimes]]\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/>\n\n==Release and promotion==\nOn April 27, 2018, after West traveled to Wyoming and made subsequent album announcements, he announced the release of the track \"[[Lift Yourself]]\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ch|first1=Devin|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-west-dedicates-upcoming-lift-yourself-track-to-ebro-news.48900.html|title=Kanye West Dedicates Upcoming 'Lift Yourself' Track To Ebro|website=HotNewHipHop|date=April 27, 2018|accessdate=April 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180428235331/https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-west-dedicates-upcoming-lift-yourself-track-to-ebro-news.48900.html|archive-date=April 28, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> That same day, the track was released on West's website, with it seeing West rap nonsensical words.<ref name=\"DeVille stereogum\">{{cite web |last1=DeVille |first1=Chris |title=Kanye West \u2013 \"Lift Yourself\" |url=https://www.stereogum.com/1993781/kanye-west-lift-yourself/music/ |website=Stereogum |accessdate=January 2, 2020 |date=April 27, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927174341/https://www.stereogum.com/1993781/kanye-west-lift-yourself/music/ |archive-date=September 27, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Graham|first1=Chris|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/artists/trollyewest-kanye-west-drops-new-song-lift-lyrics-unexpected/|title=Kanye West drops new song Lift Yourself \u2013 and its lyrics are unexpected|website=The Daily Telegraph|date=April 28, 2018|accessdate=April 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180428044438/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/artists/trollyewest-kanye-west-drops-new-song-lift-lyrics-unexpected/|archive-date=April 28, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> West premiered a track two hours after \"Lift Yourself\" titled \"[[Ye vs. the People]]\", which features fellow rapper [[T.I.]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wang|first1=Amy B|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2018/04/28/kanye-west-defends-pro-trump-remarks-in-new-song-ye-vs-the-people/?noredirect=on|title=Kanye West defends pro-Trump remarks in new song 'Ye vs. the People'|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=April 28, 2018|accessdate=April 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628100634/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2018/04/28/kanye-west-defends-pro-trump-remarks-in-new-song-ye-vs-the-people/?noredirect=on|archive-date=June 28, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> During an interview with ''[[The Breakfast Club (radio show)|The Breakfast Club]]'' in May 2018, Pusha T claimed that a version of \"Lift Yourself\" with actual lyrics exists and indicated that it could be released on the album.<ref>{{cite news|last=Britton|first=Luke Morgan|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/kanye-west-might-release-version-lift-actual-lyrics-2326902|title=Kanye West might release a version of 'Lift Yourself' with actual lyrics|work=NME|date=May 28, 2018|accessdate=September 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927174340/https://www.nme.com/news/music/kanye-west-might-release-version-lift-actual-lyrics-2326902|archive-date=September 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, ''Ye'' was later released without the song included.<ref name=\"AM\"/> It was also rumored for \"Ye vs. the People\" to be released on the album, though the song ultimately wasn't part of it.<ref name=\"AM\"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=DeVille|first1=Chris|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1993790/kanye-west-ye-vs-the-people-feat-t-i/music/|title=Kanye West \u2013 \"Ye Vs. The People\" (Feat. T.I.)|work=Stereogum|date=April 28, 2018|accessdate=September 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927174337/https://www.stereogum.com/1993790/kanye-west-ye-vs-the-people-feat-t-i/music/|archive-date=September 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A song titled \"Extacy\" was part of the original track list for ''Ye'' as the second track, though the position was taken up by \"Yikes\" instead of the song on the final release of the album, while \"Extacy\" was later released under the title of \"[[XTCY]]\" on August 11, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Miller |first1=Matt |title=Kanye West's New Song 'XTCY' Is Objectively Unpleasant |url=https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/music/a22876749/kanye-west-xtcy-song-listen/ |work=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |date=August 30, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906041447/https://www.esquire.com/entertainment/music/a22876749/kanye-west-xtcy-song-listen/ |archive-date=September 6, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kreps |first1=Daniel |title=Kanye West Drops Surprise New Song 'XTCY' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/kanye-west-drops-surprise-new-song-xtcy-710165/ |work=Rolling Stone |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |date=August 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180909133441/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/kanye-west-drops-surprise-new-song-xtcy-710165/ |archive-date=September 9, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n''Ye'' was released for [[Music download|digital download]] and [[Streaming media|streaming]] worldwide on June 1, 2018, through West's labels [[GOOD Music]] and [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]].<ref name=\"various\"/> The album was later released as a [[Compact disc|CD]] in various countries by the aforementioned labels on July 20, 2018.<ref name=\"compactdisc\"/> On June 8, it was revealed that ''Ye'' was slated to be released on [[Phonograph record|vinyl]] in the summer of 2018 and pre-orders were made available simultaneously, while the vinyl release ultimately occurred in various countries on July 27, 2018 through West's labels.<ref name=\"vinyl\">{{cite news|last1=Spice|first1=Anton|url=https://thevinylfactory.com/news/kanye-west-ye-vinyl/|title=Kanye West to release new album ye on vinyl|publisher=[[The Vinyl Factory]]|date=June 8, 2018|accessdate=October 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020121938/https://thevinylfactory.com/news/kanye-west-ye-vinyl/|archive-date=October 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"az\"/> This marked the first official vinyl release for an album by West since his collaborative studio album ''[[Watch the Throne]]'' with [[Jay-Z]] in 2011.<ref name=\"vinyl\"/> However, West's previous two albums ''Yeezus'' and ''The Life of Pablo'' were heavily [[Bootleg recording|bootlegged]] on vinyl.<ref name=\"vinyl\"/>\n[[File:Chris Rock WE 2012 Shankbone.JPG|thumb|left|170px|alt=[[Chris Rock]] at the 2012 premiere of ''What to Expect When You're Expecting'' in New York|[[Chris Rock]] announced the album as being titled ''Ye'', and narrated the video of the listening party on West's website.]]\nA two-hour listening party took place for ''Ye'' on the night of May 31, 2018 in Jackson Hole, with West broadcasting a livestream of the party through the WAV app.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Eustice|first1=Kyle|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.47094/title.kanye-west-streams-album-listening-party-on-wav-app|title=Kanye West Streams Album Listening Party on WAV App|website=HipHopDX|date=May 31, 2018|accessdate=December 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219131959/https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.47094/title.kanye-west-streams-album-listening-party-on-wav-app|archive-date=December 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> West invited a variety of guests to the listening party, including Ty Dolla Sign, Kid Cudi, Nas, Pusha T, [[Desiigner]], [[2 Chainz]], Big Sean, [[Cyhi the Prynce]], among others. Members of Def Jam's staff mobilized and organized people from various locations around the world for the party, though the number of people originally planned to fly out for it was 300 until the number was ultimately halved. At the location of the listening party, the album's title was announced as being ''Ye'' by American comedian [[Chris Rock]], shortly before the party began.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Aswad|first1=Jen|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/news/kanyes-new-album-wyoming-1202827035/|title=Live Updates From Kanye West's Album Listening Party in Wyoming|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=May 31, 2018|accessdate=June 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180607200241/https://variety.com/2018/music/news/kanyes-new-album-wyoming-1202827035/|archive-date=June 7, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Promotional videos===\nBy June 6, 2018, West's official website had been updated to include footage from the listening party for ''Ye''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Schatz|first1=Lake|title=Kanye West announces #ProjectWyoming listening parties across the US|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/06/kanye-projectwyoming-listening-party-global/|website=Consequence of Sound|date=June 6, 2018|accessdate=December 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219072536/https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/06/kanye-projectwyoming-listening-party-global/|archive-date=December 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A promotional video of the listening party was played on the website, set to the album tracks \"I Thought About Killing You\" and \"Ghost Town\". Rock provided narration for the video.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Markowitz|first1=Douglas|url=https://www.miaminewtimes.com/music/kanye-west-is-hosting-something-in-miami-tonight-10416347|title=Kanye West Project Wyoming Miami Event and Venue UPDATED|newspaper=[[Miami New Times]]|date=June 6, 2018|accessdate=December 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219072544/https://www.miaminewtimes.com/music/kanye-west-is-hosting-something-in-miami-tonight-10416347|archive-date=December 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> West's website was later updated on October 22, 2019 in promotion of his ninth studio album ''[[Jesus Is King]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Caraan|first1=Sophie|url=https://hypebeast.com/2019/10/kanye-west-jesus-is-king-new-release-date-album-pre-order|title=Kanye West 'Jesus Is King' New Release Date|website=Hypebeast|date=October 22, 2019|accessdate=December 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022181150/https://hypebeast.com/2019/10/kanye-west-jesus-is-king-new-release-date-album-pre-order|archive-date=October 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThere weren't any music videos released for ''Ye'', but [[lyric videos]] for the tracks \"All Mine\" and \"Violent Crimes\" were officially released simultaneously on June 19, 2018.<ref name=\"fader\">{{cite web |last1=Renshaw |first1=David |url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/06/19/kanye-west-violent-crimes-all-mine-ye-lyric-videos |title=Kanye West shares two ye lyric videos |work=The Fader |date=June 19, 2018 |accessdate=December 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180930115856/https://www.thefader.com/2018/06/19/kanye-west-violent-crimes-all-mine-ye-lyric-videos |archive-date=September 30, 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Both of the tracks were treated as singles from the album with the promotion, despite not having been released as such at the time, though \"All Mine\" later experienced a single release.<ref name=\"videorelease\"/><ref name=\"rhythmic\"/> The videos include the lyrics being written out on the same Wyoming mountain range displayed on the artwork for ''Ye'', while the lyrics are in the same font used for the text on the artwork.<ref name=\"fader\"/>\n\n==Singles==\nWest initially debuted ''Ye'' on June 1, 2018 without any singles, as is popular among musicians using the sudden release option that don't want a big marketing roll out.<ref name=\"auto\"/> On June 8, \"Yikes\" was released to UK [[Contemporary hit radio|mainstream radio]] stations by West's labels as the lead single from the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio1/playlist |title=BBC \u2013 Radio 1 \u2013 Playlist |publisher=[[BBC Radio 1]] |date=June 1, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180609143302/http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio1/playlist |archivedate=June 9, 2018 |accessdate=July 2, 2019}}</ref> Three days later, it was revealed that West had to choose a lead single in the United States for promotion.<ref name=\"auto\"/> Simultaneously, the song was revealed to have been selected by West for release as a single in the US.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|last1=Parizot|first1=Matthew|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-west-chooses-yikes-as-the-first-single-off-ye-news.52360.html|title=Kanye West Reportedly Chooses \"Yikes\" As The First Single Off \"Ye\"|website=HotNewHipHop|date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=June 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411200655/https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-west-chooses-yikes-as-the-first-single-off-ye-news.52360.html|archive-date=April 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was serviced to US [[Airplay|radio]] stations through West's labels as the lead single on June 11, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|author=Navjosh|url=http://hiphop-n-more.com/2018/06/kanye-west-picks-yikes-as-lead-single-from-ye/|title=Kanye West Picks 'Yikes' As Lead Single from 'ye'|work=HipHop-N-More|date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=October 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612211204/http://hiphop-n-more.com/2018/06/kanye-west-picks-yikes-as-lead-single-from-ye/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to release as a single, the song charted at number eight on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], standing as West's first solo track to enter the top ten of the Hot 100 since the single \"[[Heartless (Kanye West song)|Heartless]]\" in 2008 and becoming his 16th top ten single on the chart.<ref>{{cite web |author=Doomkitty |url=http://www.billboardradio.cn/chart/20-June-2018-US-Top-10-Singles-Billboard-hot-100-en |title=US Top 10 Singles |work=[[Billboard China|Billboard Radio China]] |accessdate=July 2, 2019 |date=June 20, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628195805/http://www.billboardradio.cn/chart/20-June-2018-US-Top-10-Singles-Billboard-hot-100-en |archive-date=June 28, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> After having been released as a single, the song made its debut at number ten on the [[UK Singles Chart]], standing as West's 19th top ten single on the chart.<ref name=\"chart\"/> On August 14, 2019, \"Yikes\" was certified [[RIAA certification|platinum]] in the US by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for sales of 1,000,000 certified units.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Kanye+West&ti=Yikes#search_section|title=Gold & Platinum \u2013 Kanye West \u2013 Yikes|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nWest went on to select \"All Mine\" for release as the second single from ''Ye'' on July 20, 2018, which features vocals by Ty Dolla Sign and Clemons.<ref name=\"Tidal\"/><ref name=\"hhnm\">{{cite news |author=Navjosh |url=http://hiphop-n-more.com/2018/07/kanye-west-all-mine-next-single-from-ye/ |title=Kanye West Picks 'All Mine' As Next Single From 'ye' |work=HipHop-N-More |date=July 20, 2018 |accessdate=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724154100/http://hiphop-n-more.com/2018/07/kanye-west-all-mine-next-single-from-ye/ |archive-date=July 24, 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> This decision was made by West due to his labels preparing a track for such a release to block a momentum loss for the album after \"Yikes\" experienced a lack of success on record charts.<ref name=\"hhnm\"/> However, the track's lyric video had been released in promotion over a month before it was selected for release as a single.<ref name=\"videorelease\">{{cite news |last1=Zidel |first1=Alex |title=Kanye West Releases New Lyric Videos For 'Violent Crimes' & \"All Mine\" |url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-west-releases-new-lyric-videos-for-violent-crimes-and-all-mine-news.53002.html |website=HotNewHipHop |date=June 19, 2019 |accessdate=October 22, 2019 }}</ref> On July 24, 2018, the track was sent to US [[rhythmic contemporary]] radio stations through West's labels as the second single.<ref name=\"rhythmic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|title=Top 40 Rhythmic Future Releases|publisher=AllAccess.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180719210657/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|archivedate=July 19, 2018|accessdate=July 20, 2018}}</ref> The track entered at number 11 on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100, prior to being released as a single.<ref name=\"debut\"/> That same week, the track also debuted at number 11 on the UK Singles Chart.<ref name=\"chart\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/14958/kanye-west/|title=Kanye West full Official Chart History|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=June 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617041308/http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/14958/kanye-west/|archive-date=June 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> \"All Mine\" was certified platinum in the US by the RIAA for selling 1,000,000 certified units on September 21, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Kanye+West&ti=All+Mine#search_section|title=Gold & Platinum \u2013 Kanye West \u2013 All Mine|publisher=RIAA|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> On March 6, 2020, the track was certified silver in the United Kingdom by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI) for sales of 200,000 units.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bpi.co.uk/award/16254-997-1|title=Award \u2013 Kanye West \u2013 All Mine|publisher=[[British Phonographic Industry|BPI]]|accessdate=October 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329111013/https://www.bpi.co.uk/award/16254-997-1|archive-date=March 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBoth of the singles stood as West's first entries in the top ten of the US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart since \"[[All Day (Kanye West song)|All Day]]\" reached number six in 2015.<ref name=\"twenty\">{{cite news |last1=Anderson |first1=Trevor |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8461085/kanye-west-ye-aretha-franklin-top-40-total-hot-rb-hip-hop-songs-chart |title=Kanye West Passes Aretha Franklin's Top 40 Total on Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs |date=June 14, 2018 |website=Billboard |accessdate=July 2, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702002638/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8461085/kanye-west-ye-aretha-franklin-top-40-total-hot-rb-hip-hop-songs-chart |archive-date=July 2, 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> \"Yikes\" and \"All Mine\" gave West his 25th and 26th tracks to attain top ten positions on the chart, entering at number seven and nine, respectively.<ref name=\"twenty\"/> Though \"Yikes\" charted higher than \"All Mine\", the latter remained on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100 longer; it spend nine weeks on the chart, while the former only remained on the Hot 100 for five weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Kanye-West/chart-history/hot-100/song/1081874|title=Kanye West \u2013 All Mine \u2013 Chart History|work=Billboard|accessdate=July 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830220422/https://www.billboard.com/music/Kanye-West/chart-history/hot-100/song/1081874|archive-date=August 30, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Kanye-West/chart-history/hot-100/song/1081861|title=Kanye West \u2013 Yikes \u2013 Chart History|work=Billboard|accessdate=July 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419114910/https://www.billboard.com/music/Kanye-West/chart-history/hot-100/song/1081861|archive-date=April 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Artwork and title==\n[[File:Barns grand tetons.jpg|thumb|right|alt=The [[Mormon Row Historic District|John Moulton Barn]] on Mormon Row at the base of the [[Teton Range|Grand Tetons]], [[Wyoming]].|A view of the [[Teton Range]] from the [[Jackson Hole]] valley, similar to the view depicted in the cover art for ''Ye''.]] \nThe artwork for ''Ye'' was revealed by Kardashian to have been taken by West on his [[iPhone]] on their way to the listening party on May 31, 2018, hours before the release of the album. It features a view of the [[Teton Range]] from Jackson Hole, the mountain range where the album was recorded and produced.<ref name=\"people\"/> The mountainous terrain photographed is natural, though it is questionable whether the artwork includes a skyline or not within the area that the terrain is present on it.<ref>{{cite web |author=Hattis, Hunter |url=https://vulture.com/2018/06/kanye-took-the-photo-on-his-new-ye-album-cover-himself.html |title=Kanye Took the Photo on His New Album Cover Himself |publisher=[[Vulture.com|Vulture]] |date=June 1, 2018 |accessdate=December 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106221843/http://www.vulture.com/2018/06/kanye-took-the-photo-on-his-new-ye-album-cover-himself.html |archive-date=November 6, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The text on the artwork reads: \"I hate being / Bi-Polar / its awesome,\" {{sic}} which is scribbled in neon green over the mountain range.<ref name=\"people\">{{cite web |last1=Mizoguchi |first1=Karen |last2=White |first2=Chelsea |last3=Telling |first3=Gillian |url=https://people.com/music/kanye-west-new-album-ye-released-after-twitter-rants-controversies |title=Kanye West Raps About Kim Kardashian West Leaving Him, Bipolar Disorder in 7-Track Album YE |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=June 1, 2018 |accessdate=June 1, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180601100121/https://people.com/music/kanye-west-new-album-ye-released-after-twitter-rants-controversies/ |archive-date=June 1, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> With the inclusion of the phrase on the artwork, West blatantly confirmed his bipolar disorder.<ref name=\"health\">{{cite web |last1=Basu |first1=Tanya |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/kanye-wests-bipolar-disorder-and-the-shaky-science-of-the-tortured-genius |title=Kanye West's Bipolar Disorder and the Shaky Science of the 'Tortured Genius' |work=[[The Daily Beast]] |date=June 1, 2018 |accessdate=December 18, 2019 }}</ref>\n\nIn an interview conducted with [[Big Boy (rapper)|Big Boy]] during the listening party for the album, West explained the title, which is a [[diminutive]] of his own name commonly used in his songs, by stating: \"I believe 'ye' is the most commonly used word in the [[Bible]], and in the Bible it means 'you.' So I'm you, I'm us, it's us. It went from Kanye, which means 'the only one,' to just ''Ye'' \u2013 just being a reflection of our good, our bad, our confused, everything.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-kanye-west-talk-ye-mental-health-in-new-interview-w521025|title=Watch Kanye West Talk 'Ye,' Mental Health in New Interview|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=June 3, 2018|accessdate=June 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613062555/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-kanye-west-talk-ye-mental-health-in-new-interview-w521025|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> However, West was incorrect in his belief of \"ye\" being the most commonly used word in the Bible.<ref name=\"ew\"/> West went on to tweet out in June 2018 that without his ego, he is \"Just ''Ye'',\" potentially giving context into why the album is titled as such.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Holmes |first1=Charles |title=Did Kanye Just Reveal Who He 'Thought About Killing' On That Ye Track? |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3079682/kanye-west-i-thought-about-killing-you-ye-track/ |access-date=December 18, 2019 |publisher=MTV |date=June 14, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190217142450/http://www.mtv.com/news/3079682/kanye-west-i-thought-about-killing-you-ye-track/ |archive-date=February 17, 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 6.1/10<ref name=\"ADM\">{{cite web|url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/9371/Kanye-West-Ye.aspx|title=Ye by Kanye West reviews|publisher=[[AnyDecentMusic?]]|accessdate=June 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143241/http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/9371/Kanye-West-Ye.aspx|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| MC = 64/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/ye/kanye-west|title=Ye by Kanye West Reviews and Tracks|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=June 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180609032608/http://www.metacritic.com/music/ye/kanye-west|archive-date=June 9, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|2.5|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|last=Yeung|first=Neil Z.|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/ye-mw0003181816|title=Ye \u2013 Kanye West|publisher=AllMusic|accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403080453/https://www.allmusic.com/album/ye-mw0003181816|archive-date=April 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev2Score = B<ref name=\"AVClub\">{{cite web|last=Purdom|first=Clayton|url=https://music.avclub.com/ye-won-t-change-your-mind-on-kanye-1826486318|title=Ye won't change your mind on Kanye|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=June 1, 2018|accessdate=June 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190928211817/https://music.avclub.com/ye-won-t-change-your-mind-on-kanye-1826486318|archive-date=September 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Telegraph\">{{cite news|last=Jones|first=Lucy|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/artists/kanye-west-ye-review-dynamic-narration-worst-year-yet/|title=Never mind his politics, the old Kanye is back \u2013 Ye, review|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=June 1, 2018|accessdate=June 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180601144346/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/artists/kanye-west-ye-review-dynamic-narration-worst-year-yet/|archive-date=June 1, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| rev4Score = C+<ref name=\"ew\">{{cite magazine|last=Suskind|first=Alex|url=http://ew.com/music/2018/06/05/kanye-ye-review/|title=The depressing dogma of Kanye West's Ye: EW review|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=June 5, 2018|accessdate=June 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180609040625/https://ew.com/music/2018/06/05/kanye-ye-review/|archive-date=June 9, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev5Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Guardian\">{{cite web|last=Petridis|first=Alexis|authorlink=Alexis Petridis|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jun/01/kanye-west-ye-review-good-music|title=Kanye West: ye review \u2013 a candid tour of a troubled mind|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=June 1, 2018|accessdate=June 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329214326/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jun/01/kanye-west-ye-review-good-music|archive-date=March 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev6score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{cite news|last=Hooton|first=Christopher|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/kanye-west-ye-album-review-critic-reaction-070-shake-wyoming-a8385666.html|title='ye' album review: Kanye West flew too close to the sun, then directly into it|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|date=June 8, 2018|accessdate=June 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622190616/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/kanye-west-ye-album-review-critic-reaction-070-shake-wyoming-a8385666.html|archive-date=June 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev7score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web|last=Greenwood|first=Douglas|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/kanye-west-ye-review-2331315|title=Kanye West \u2013 'ye' review|work=NME|date=June 3, 2018|accessdate=December 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180604002714/http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/kanye-west-ye-review|archive-date=June 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[The Observer]]''\n| rev8score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"Observer\">{{cite news|last=Empire|first=Kitty|authorlink=Kitty Empire|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jun/02/ye-kanye-west-review-self-righteous-soulful-shocking|title=Kanye West: Ye review \u2013 self-righteous, soulful and still shocking|newspaper=[[The Observer]]|date=June 2, 2018|accessdate=September 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906120614/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jun/02/ye-kanye-west-review-self-righteous-soulful-shocking|archive-date=September 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev9score = 7.1/10<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|last=Garvey|first=Meaghan|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/kanye-west-ye|title=Kanye West: ye|work=Pitchfork|date=June 4, 2018|accessdate=June 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904180019/https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/kanye-west-ye/|archive-date=September 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev10score = {{rating|2.5|5}}<ref name=\"RollingStone\">{{cite magazine|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|authorlink=Rob Sheffield|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/review-kanye-west-ye-album-rob-sheffield-review-w521089|title=Review: Kanye West's Chaotic, Insecure 'Ye'|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=June 5, 2018|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614055401/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/review-kanye-west-ye-album-rob-sheffield-review-w521089|archive-date=June 14, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n''Ye'' was met with generally favorable reviews from [[Music journalism|music critics]]. At [[Metacritic]], the album received an [[weighted arithmetic mean|average]] score of 64, based on 34 reviews.<ref name=\"MC\"/> Aggregator [[AnyDecentMusic?]] gave it 6.1 out of 10, based on their assessment of the critical consensus.<ref name=\"ADM\"/>\n\n[[Alexis Petridis]] for ''[[The Guardian]]'' stated the album doesn't feel slight, but opined that it is exhausting. Petridis wrote: \"Substantially more focused than its predecessor, it packs a lot into 23 minutes. It is bold, risky, infuriating, compelling and a little exhausting: a vivid reflection of its author.\"<ref name=\"Guardian\"/> Jones looked at ''Ye'' as \"an album about Kanye's state of mind, his family, and a narration of what's been going on in his 'shaky-ass year.' The beats are great. Lyrically, it's fine. Whatever you think of his politics, his songwriting, sample-hunting and beat-making remain dynamic, surprising and ballsy.\"<ref name=\"Telegraph\"/> Purdom claimed that West \"can still create thunderous blasts of sound on par with anyone on the planet, and ''Ye''{{'}}s best moments are reminders of that. It's a prismatic album, reflecting its creator's entire body of work\u2014and also whatever you think about him going in.\"<ref name=\"AVClub\"/> Writing for ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'', [[Maura Johnston]] compared West's previous projects to the album, saying that \"the one thing they've consistently focused on is contrast: light and dark, ugly and beautiful, self-aggrandizing and self-loathing.\"<ref name=\"maura\"/> She added that it \"resembles his last album, ''The Life of Pablo'' in which ''Ye'' doesn't deviate too much from the lyrical concepts of ''Pablo''; it blends the trivial and the life-or-death, like on the darkened-club 'Yikes,' on which he declares his bipolar syndrome to be his 'superpower' and compares the U.S.-North Korea tensions to his long-simmering beef with [[Wiz Khalifa]].\"<ref name=\"maura\">{{cite magazine|last=Johnston|first=Maura|authorlink=Maura Johnston|url=http://ezproxy.aacc.edu/login?url=http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=aph&AN=129997295&site=ehost-live&scope=site|title=On Ye, Kanye West Is Still a Tangle of Contradictions|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|volume=191|issue=23|date=June 18, 2018|accessdate=November 20, 2018|page=62|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Kyle Mullin from ''[[Exclaim!]]'' wrote that \"if West had better delved into his emotional and psychological turmoil in ''Ye''{{'}}s lyrics, instead of getting bogged down with click-baity asides, then this LP would've been a classic.\"<ref name=\"Exclaim\">{{cite web|last=Mullin|first=Kyle|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/kanye_west-ye|title=Kanye West: ye|work=[[Exclaim!]]|date=June 3, 2018|accessdate=June 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812021423/http://exclaim.ca/music/article/kanye_west-ye|archive-date=August 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nEric Brown was less enthusiastic in ''Billboard'', stating: \"It's tough to ignore ''Ye''{{'}}s musical stasis; known for his forward motion, on this set, West remains mired in the past,\" also commenting that \"It's a missed opportunity in the sense that it fails to measure up to his previous work and change the conversation around him.\"<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite magazine|last=Brown|first=Eric Renner|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8459073/kanye-west-ye-missed-opportunity-review|title=Kanye West's 'Ye' Review: Why the Album Is a Missed Opportunity for Redemption|magazine=Billboard|date=June 4, 2018|accessdate=June 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613005231/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8459073/kanye-west-ye-missed-opportunity-review|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> For [[AllMusic]], Neil Z. Yeung expressed mixed feelings, writing that the album \"can feel uneven, sometimes boring, and more indulgent than usual, but it's a fascinating peek into West's psyche.\"<ref name=\"AM\"/> Similarly, Wren Graves of ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' believed that \"on ''Ye'', he's consolidating old skills, not testing out new ones,\" adding that \"the lack of wow-factor, combined with the short length, makes the album feel somewhat slight.\"<ref name=\"CoS\">{{cite web|last=Graves|first=Wren|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/06/album-review-kanye-west-ye|title=Kanye West Proves Less Is So Much More on ye|work=Consequence of Sound|date=June 5, 2018|accessdate=June 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140339/https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/06/album-review-kanye-west-ye/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Rob Sheffield]] of ''Rolling Stone'' described the album as \"wildly uneven\" with \"enough sporadic flashes of brilliance to make you hungry for much, much more.\"<ref name=\"RollingStone\"/> ''[[Slant Magazine]]''{{'}}s Zachary Hoskins viewed the album as what \"just feels unfinished, as if he wanted to avoid another debacle like the rollout of the also-unfinished ''The Life of Pablo''\" and called it \"a mix of the weakest moments from ''The Life of Pablo''.\"<ref name=\"slant\">{{cite web|last=Hoskins|first=Zachary|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/kanye-west-ye|title=Kanye West: Ye|work=[[Slant Magazine]]|date=June 1, 2018|accessdate=June 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180608202736/https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/kanye-west-ye|archive-date=June 8, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Horton wrote negatively of the album, claiming that \"there's no through-line. No concept. No consistency. There's certainly no quality control.\"<ref name=\"line\">{{cite web|last=Horton|first=Ross|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/ye-is-not-the-kanye-you-love-its-the-kanye-we-deserve|title=ye is not the Kanye you love \u2013 it's the Kanye we deserve|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|date=June 2, 2018|accessdate=June 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203132318/https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/ye-is-not-the-kanye-you-love-its-the-kanye-we-deserve|archive-date=February 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Robert Christgau]] gave the album a [[Christgau's Consumer Guide: Albums of the '90s#Grading key|one-star honorable mention]] in a [[capsule review|capsule-review]] column for ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'', calling it a \"half-assed attempt to make [[wikt:asshat|asshattery]] germane again.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/ev8nvz/robert-christgau-reviews-pusha-t-kanye-west-tierra-whack|title=Robert Christgau on G.O.O.D Music's Good (and Less Good) Music|magazine=Vice|date=July 13, 2018|accessdate=July 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180714081757/https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/ev8nvz/robert-christgau-reviews-pusha-t-kanye-west-tierra-whack|archive-date=July 14, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n''Ye'' appeared on year-end best album lists for 2018 by multiple publications. On the ''Pitchfork'' Readers' Poll: Top 50 Albums of 2018, the album was voted in at number 37.<ref name=\"readers\">{{cite web |title=Pitchfork Readers' Poll Results 2018 |url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/pitchfork-readers-poll-results-2018/ |website=Pitchfork |date=December 24, 2018 |accessdate=August 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181227150512/https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/pitchfork-readers-poll-results-2018/ |archive-date=December 27, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Ye'' was listed at number four on the website's polls for most underrated and most overrated album of the year, respectively.<ref name=\"readers\"/> It was ranked at the same position on ''[[GQ]]'' Russia's list of 2018's best albums.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.ru/entertainment/best-music-albums-2018|title=\u041b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0438\u0435 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0430\u043b\u044c\u0431\u043e\u043c\u044b 2018 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430|work=[[GQ]] (Russia)|language=Russian|date=November 28, 2018|accessdate=February 6, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206015655/https://www.gq.ru/entertainment/best-music-albums-2018|archive-date=February 6, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[The Edge (magazine)|The Edge]]'' and Jon Caramanica of ''[[The New York Times]]'' both listed the album as the seventh best of the year.<ref name=\"edge\">{{cite web |last=Law |first=Sam |url=https://www.theedgesusu.co.uk/records/2018/12/25/the-edges-top-albums-of-2018-kanye-west-ye/ |title=The Edge's Top Albums of 2018: Kanye West \u2212 ye |website=[[The Edge (magazine)|The Edge]] |date=December 25, 2018 |accessdate=October 21, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924142548/https://www.theedgesusu.co.uk/records/2018/12/25/the-edges-top-albums-of-2018-kanye-west-ye/ |archive-date=September 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Pareles |first1=Jon |last2=Caramanica |first2=Jon |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/06/arts/music/best-albums.html |title=The 28 Best Albums of 2018 |website=The New York Times |date=December 6, 2018 |accessdate=October 21, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181213202225/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/06/arts/music/best-albums.html |archivedate=December 13, 2018 }}</ref> ''Ye'' was ranked by ''NME'' as the 34th best album of 2018, with the staff writing that \"there's plenty in this [[Experimental music|experimental]], weird little album that suggests Kanye has very much still got it.\"<ref name=\"NME - Best albums of the year 2018\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/best-greatest-albums-of-the-year-2018-2419656 |title=Best albums of the year 2018 |website=NME |date=December 13, 2018 |accessdate=October 19, 2019 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190111173128/https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/best-greatest-albums-of-the-year-2018-2419656 |archive-date=January 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''411Mania'' named ''Ye'' the 42nd best album of the year, with David Hayter of the website claiming that despite the \"serious faults\" of the album, it is an \"endlessly listenable collection,\" calling the music \"too coherent and sonically satisfying to quibble over.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hayter |first1=David |title=The Top 100 Albums of 2018 (60-41): Kanye West, Black Panther, More |url=https://411mania.com/music/top-100-albums-of-2018-60-41-kanye-west-black-panther-more/ |website=411Mania |date=December 21, 2018 |accessdate=August 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190807081149/https://411mania.com/music/top-100-albums-of-2018-60-41-kanye-west-black-panther-more/ |archive-date=August 7, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Ye'' was ranked as the 30th best hip hop album of 2018 by ''Rolling Stone'' even though the staff viewed it as West's worst album, writing that \"West, at his worst, is still making more fascinating music than almost anyone else,\" and the staff elaborated, calling the album \"a dense and, at times, brilliant piece of music.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Weingaten |first1=Christopher R. |last2=Klinkenberg |first2=Brendan |last3=Holmes |first3=Charles |last4=Reeves |last5=Mosi |title=Hip-Hop: 30 Best of 2018 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/30-best-hip-hop-albums-of-2018-771909/city-girls-period-771922/ |website=Rolling Stone |date=December 26, 2018 |accessdate=August 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190324190023/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/30-best-hip-hop-albums-of-2018-771909/ |archive-date=March 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn April 25, 2018, West tweeted out: \"I'm turn the [[Grammy Award|Grammys]] into the Yammys,\" predicting success for himself at the [[61st Annual Grammy Awards|2019 Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Are|first=Tone|url=https://www.vladtv.com/article/244261/kanye-predicts-he-will-own-the-2019-grammys|title=Kanye Predicts He Will Own The 2019 Grammy's|publisher=[[DJ Vlad|Vlad TV]]|date=April 26, 2018|accessdate=October 20, 2019}}</ref> West's work on ''Ye'' and other projects earned him a nomination for [[Grammy Award for Producer of the Year, Non-Classical|Producer of the Year, Non-Classical]] at the ceremony.<ref>{{cite news|last=Orcutt|first=KC|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/12/kanye-west-pharrell-nominated-producer-2019-grammy-awards/|title=Kanye West and More Nominated for Producer of the Year Grammy|website=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|date=December 7, 2018|accessdate=October 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190813231808/https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/12/kanye-west-pharrell-nominated-producer-2019-grammy-awards/|archive-date=August 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the album marked West's first to not be nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Album|Best Rap Album]] at the Grammys, with the lack of a nomination being viewed as a snub by multiple publications.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/kanye-west|title=Kanye West {{!}} Artist|publisher=[[Grammy Award|Grammy]]|date=February 11, 2019|accessdate=October 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220010759/https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/kanye-west|archive-date=February 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"snub\">{{cite web|last=Schatz|first=Lake|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/12/2019-grammy-snubs/|title=2019 Grammy Snubs: Ariana Grande, Kanye West, Taylor Swift shut out|website=Consequence of Sound|date=December 7, 2018|accessdate=September 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190922141548/https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/12/2019-grammy-snubs/|archive-date=September 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Weiss|first=Sabrina Rojas|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/02/223626/kim-kardashian-kanye-west-going-to-grammys-2019|title=Are Kim Kardashian & Kanye West at the 2019 Grammys?|publisher=[[Refinery29]]|date=February 10, 2019|accessdate=September 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190922141549/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/02/223626/kim-kardashian-kanye-west-going-to-grammys-2019|archive-date=September 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=McDermott|first=Maeve|url=https://usatoday.com/story/life/music/2018/12/07/2019-grammys-snubs-beyonce-and-jay-z-taylor-swift-and-more-shockers/2229055002/|title=2019 Grammys snubs: Beyonce and Jay-Z, Taylor Swift, Ariana Grande and more shockers|website=[[USA Today]]|date=December 17, 2018|accessdate=September 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190922143107/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2018/12/07/2019-grammys-snubs-beyonce-and-jay-z-taylor-swift-and-more-shockers/2229055002/|archive-date=September 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Baty|first=Emma|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/a26105222/kanye-west-skipped-grammys-2019/|title=Why Kanye West Didn't Show Up to the Grammys This Year \u2013 Did Kanye Skip the Grammys?|website=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|date=February 11, 2019|accessdate=September 24, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924100829/https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/a26105222/kanye-west-skipped-grammys-2019/|archive-date=September 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In an article for ''Consequence of Sound'', Lake Schatz was surprised by West being snubbed even though he called ''Ye'' \"hardly the best in his catalog\" and questioned \"whether the lack of even a nomination has to do partially with the MC's especially divisive nature in 2018.\"<ref name=\"snub\"/> At the 2019 [[Hungarian Music Awards|Fonogram Hungarian Music Awards]], the album earned a nomination for Best Foreign Rap or Hip-Hop Album of the Year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Candidates 2019 |url=http://www.fonogram.hu/jeloltek |language=Hungarian |website=Fonogram |accessdate=September 22, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407203151/http://www.fonogram.hu/jeloltek |archivedate=April 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''Ye'' debuted at number one on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 208,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, of which 85,000 were pure album sales, giving it the fifth-largest weekly sales of an album for 2018 at the time in terms of units, and simultaneously entered atop the US [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]] chart.<ref name=\"Caulfield\"/><ref name=\"dx\"/> The album was West's eighth consecutive chart topper on the ''Billboard'' 200, helping him tie [[Eminem]]'s still active-streak from 2000 to 2018 and English band [[the Beatles]] streak from 1965\u20131968 as one of only three acts to accumulate eight consecutive number one albums.<ref name=\"Caulfield\"/> West also became the only other act apart from Eminem to achieve eight consecutive number one debuts, since none of the albums from the Beatles' streak debuted atop the ''Billboard'' 200, while tying Eminem for the second position of most number one albums among rappers.<ref name=\"Caulfield\"/> The sales surpassed the first week projections of 175,000 to 190,000 album-equivalent units and up to 80,000 pure sales.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zidel |first1=Alex |title=Kanye West's \"Ye\" Projected First Week Sales Are Astonishingly High |url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/kanye-wests-ye-projected-first-week-sales-are-astonishingly-high-news.51771.html |accessdate=October 21, 2019 |website=HotNewHipHop |date=June 4, 2018 }}</ref> ''Ye'' recorded the second largest per-track streaming average ever, receiving 25.7&nbsp;million on-demand audio streams.<ref name=\"Caulfield\">{{cite magazine |last1=Caulfield |first1=Keith |title=Kanye West Earns Eighth No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Ye' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8460189/kanye-west-eighth-no-1-album-billboard-200-ye |accessdate=June 12, 2018 |magazine=Billboard |date=June 10, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180611001709/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8460189/kanye-west-eighth-no-1-album-billboard-200-ye |archivedate=June 11, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> The seventh-largest streaming debut week ever was experienced with 120,000 streaming equivalent albums, with the streams being counted at over 180 million.<ref name=\"Caulfield\"/><ref name=\"dx\">{{cite news |last1=Eustice |first1=Kyle |title=Hip Hop Album Sales: Kanye West's \"ye\" Tops Billboard 200 With 5th-Biggest Week Of 2018 |url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.47222/title.hip-hop-album-sales-kanye-wests-ye-tops-billboard-200-with-5th-biggest-week-of-2018 |accessdate=October 20, 2019 |website=HipHopDX |date=June 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724221316/https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.47222/title.hip-hop-album-sales-kanye-wests-ye-tops-billboard-200-with-5th-biggest-week-of-2018 |archive-date=July 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe album descended four places to number five in its second week on the ''Billboard'' 200 and dropped 65% in sales, moving 74,000 album-equivalent units.<ref name=\"kday\">{{cite web|author=mportugal|url=https://www.935kday.com/2018/06/21/kanye-wests-ye-album-sees-a-65-sales-drop-in-its-second-week/|title=Kanye West's 'Ye' Album Sees A 65% Sales Drop in Its Second Week|publisher=[[KDAY|93.5 KDAY]]|date=June 21, 2018|accessdate=October 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919094518/http://www.935kday.com/2018/06/21/kanye-wests-ye-album-sees-a-65-sales-drop-in-its-second-week/|archive-date=September 19, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> This became the second highest decrease in sales for an album's second week of 2018, standing behind the 73% decline of American musician [[J. Cole]]'s fifth studio album ''[[KOD (album)|KOD]]''; however, the second week sales for ''KOD'' were higher than those of ''Ye'', with the album pushing 105,000 units.<ref name=\"kday\"/> The following week, ''Ye'' dropped six places to number 11, selling 36,000 album-equivalent units mostly due to streaming, while around 6,000 came from paid downloads.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Giacomazzo |first1=Bernadette |title=Hip Hop Album Sales: Beyonc\u00e9 & JAY-Z's \"EVERYTHING IS LOVE\" Debuts On Billboard 200 |url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.47407/title.hip-hop-album-sales-beyonce-jay-zs-everything-is-love-debuts-on-billboard-200# |accessdate=October 24, 2019 |website=HipHopDX |date=June 25, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625200132/https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.47407/title.hip-hop-album-sales-beyonce-jay-zs-everything-is-love-debuts-on-billboard-200 |archive-date=June 25, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Friedman|first1=Roger|url=https://www.showbiz411.com/2018/06/24/kanye-sales-collapse-in-third-week-ye-album-sells-total-only-39k-mostly-from-streaming|title=Kanye Sales Collapse: In Third Week, \"Ye\" Album Sells Total Only 39K, Mostly from Streaming|date=June 24, 2018|publisher=[[Showbiz411]]|access-date=November 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103052600/https://www.showbiz411.com/2018/06/24/kanye-sales-collapse-in-third-week-ye-album-sells-total-only-39k-mostly-from-streaming|archive-date=November 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On September 21, 2018, the album was certified gold in the US by the RIAA for selling 500,000 album-equivalent units.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Miss2Bees|url=https://thesource.com/2018/10/16/kanye-west-gold/|title=Kanye West's 'Ye', 'I Love It' Featuring Lil Pump Goes Gold|website=[[The Source]]|date=October 16, 2018|accessdate=September 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190928023616/https://thesource.com/2018/10/16/kanye-west-gold/|archive-date=September 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2018, ''Ye'' was ranked as the 50th and 30th most popular album of the year on the ''Billboard'' 200 and Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums charts respectively.<ref name=\"bb200\"/><ref name=\"bbhh\"/>\n\n''Ye'' debuted atop the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Albums]] chart, giving West his second chart-topping album in Australia and replacing fellow rapper [[Post Malone]]'s second studio album ''[[Beerbongs & Bentleys]]'' at the top position.<ref name=\"abc\">{{cite news |author1=Newstead, Al |title=Kanye West's seven-track album strategy is paying off. Here's why |url=https://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/kanye-west-1-australian-album-heres-why/9860784 |accessdate=October 22, 2019 |publisher=[[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]] |date=June 12, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181002062207/http://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/kanye-west-1-australian-album-heres-why/9860784 |archive-date=October 2, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"source\">{{cite news |author1=Sam |title=Kanye West's 'ye' Top Charts in Australia |url=https://thesource.com/2018/06/14/kanye-west-ye-austrailia/ |accessdate=November 3, 2019 |website=The Source |date=June 14, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103164551/https://thesource.com/2018/06/14/kanye-west-ye-austrailia/ |archive-date=November 3, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> This made West the third major hip hop act to have an album reach the top ten of the chart in 2018, joining J. Cole with ''KOD'' and [[ASAP Rocky]] with his third studio album ''[[Testing (album)|Testing]]''.<ref name=\"abc\"/> A Streaming Equivalent Album Value being taken into account for the Album Chart calculations in Australia helped ''Ye'' top the ARIA Albums chart, since the value counts the streams for all tracks of albums ten tracks or less, rather than the two most streamed tracks as done for longer albums.<ref name=\"abc\"/> The album was also a chart topper on the [[Irish Albums Chart]], giving West his first number one album in Ireland.<ref name=\"week\">{{cite web |author1=Jones, Alan |title=International charts analysis: Kanye West makes global impact with Ye |url=https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/international-charts-analysis-kanye-west-makes-global-impact-with-ye/072773 |accessdate=November 2, 2019 |work=[[Music Week]] |date=June 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191102224340/https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/international-charts-analysis-kanye-west-makes-global-impact-with-ye/072773 |archive-date=November 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> By reaching the same position on the [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|New Zealand Albums]] chart, ''Ye'' became West's second number one album in the country.<ref name=\"source\"/> The following week, it remained at the top position.<ref name=\"week2\">{{cite web |author1=Jones, Alan |title=International Charts Analysis: Kanye West continues to make global impact |url=https://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/international-charts-analysis-kanye-west-continues-to-make-global-impact/072849 |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |work=Music Week |date=June 18, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618013228/https://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/international-charts-analysis-kanye-west-continues-to-make-global-impact/072849 |archive-date=June 18, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> The album also debuted at number one on the [[Canadian Albums Chart]], with 16,000 total consumption units but it reached the second highest album sales and on-demand streams of the week.<ref name=\"fyi\">{{cite news|url=https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2018/06/10/coeur-de-pirate-has-weeks-best-selling-album|title=Coeur De Pirate Has This Week's Best-Selling Album|publisher=FYIMusicNews|date=June 10, 2018|accessdate=February 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204084358/https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2018/06/10/coeur-de-pirate-has-weeks-best-selling-album|archive-date=December 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> This became West's sixth chart-topping album in Canada, while also standing as his first since ''Yeezus''.<ref name=\"fyi\"/> In Estonia, ''Ye'' entered at number one on the [[Eesti Tipp-40|Albumid tipp-40]] and remained atop the chart the following week.<ref name=\"est\"/>\n\n''Ye'' entered at number two on the [[UK Albums Chart]], being held off the top spot by ''[[The Greatest Showman: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack]]''.<ref name=\"irish\"/> The soundtrack album denied West a number one album on his own birthday and prevented him from topping the chart for the third time in his career.<ref name=\"irish\">{{cite magazine |author1=Arthur, Andrew |title=The Greatest Showman denies Kanye West number one album on his birthday |url=https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/music/the-greatest-showman-denies-kanye-west-number-one-album-on-his-birthday-36990895.html |accessdate=July 3, 2019 |magazine=[[Irish Independent|Independent.ie]] |date=June 8, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703080704/https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/music/the-greatest-showman-denies-kanye-west-number-one-album-on-his-birthday-36990895.html |archive-date=July 3, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, the album was the most played album of the week on [[Streaming media|streaming services]], and it was reported that 80% of sales came from streams.<ref name=\"irish\"/> On January 4, 2019, ''Ye'' was certified silver in the UK by the BPI for sales of 60,000 units.<ref name=\"bpi\"/> The album also attained the chart position of number two on both the [[Hitlisten|Danish Albums Chart]] and [[VG-lista|Norwegian Albums Chart]].<ref name=\"week2\"/> Similarly, ''Ye'' reached number three on the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|Czech Albums]], [[Music of Iceland|Icelandic Albums]], and Netherlands' [[Dutch Album Top 100]] charts.<ref name=\"week\"/><ref name=\"week2\"/><ref name=\"ice\"/> On the [[Sverigetopplistan|Swedish Albums]] chart, the album reached number five.<ref name=\"week\"/>\n\nAll seven tracks from ''Ye'' debuted in the top 40 of the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100, with lead single \"Yikes\" charting the highest at number eight.<ref name=\"debut\"/> The tracks entering the Hot 100 lead to West's total number of top 40 entries amounting to 48, placing him joint-tenth with fellow rapper [[Jay-Z]] on the list for most top 40 entries on the chart, and also made West the eleventh act with as many as seven simultaneous top 40 Hot 100 entries.<ref name=\"debut\">{{cite magazine |author1=Trust, Gary |title=Kanye West Debuts All 7 Songs From 'Ye' in Billboard Hot 100's Top 40 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8460526/kanye-west-ye-all-7-songs-debut-hot-100-top-40 |accessdate=June 13, 2018 |magazine=Billboard |date=June 12, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612235543/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8460526/kanye-west-ye-all-7-songs-debut-hot-100-top-40 |archivedate=June 12, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> West topped the US [[List of number-one artists on the Billboard Artist 100|''Billboard'' Artist 100]] for the first time in his career, partially as a result of the entries from the album, surpassing his previous peak position of number three that was attained as a result of ''The Life of Pablo''.<ref>{{cite magazine |author1=Zellner, Xander |title=Kanye West Is No. 1 on the Artist 100 Chart |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8460755/kanye-west-no-1-artist-100-chart |accessdate=December 17, 2019 |magazine=Billboard |date=June 13, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191014063427/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8460755/kanye-west-no-1-artist-100-chart |archive-date=October 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also, all seven tracks debuted on the ARIA Singles Chart, with \"All Mine\" attaining the highest entry at number ten.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/6/aria-chart-watch-476/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #476|publisher=auspOp|date=June 9, 2018|accessdate=March 14, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416001157/https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/6/aria-chart-watch-476/|archive-date=April 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> As well as this, the two tracks \"Ghost Town\" and \"All Mine\" charted in the top 40 of the UK Singles Chart, along with \"Yikes\"; the latter was the highest charting from the album at number ten.<ref name=\"irish\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]<ref name=\"Tidal\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/98156343|title=ye / Kanye West|publisher=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=February 19, 2019|archive-url=http://archive.is/ccxYi|archive-date=March 28, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Qobuz]].<ref name=\"Qobuz\">{{cite web|url=https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/ye-kanye-west/g9bwaim4ejndb|title=ye {{!}} Kanye West \u2013 Download and listen to the album|publisher=[[Qobuz]]|accessdate=June 16, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616103404/https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/ye-kanye-west/g9bwaim4ejndb|archive-date=June 16, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| total_length = 23:41\n| title_width = 30%\n| writing_width = 35%\n| extra_width = 35%\n\n| title1 = [[I Thought About Killing You]]\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Kanye West]]|[[Mike Dean (record producer)|Mike Dean]]|[[Francis Farewell Starlite]]|[[Benny Blanco|Benjamin Levin]]|[[Cyhi the Prynce|Cydel Young]]|[[Consequence (rapper)|Dexter Mills]]|[[Malik Yusef]]|[[Wiley (musician)|Richard Cowie]]|[[Skepta|Joseph Adenuga Olaitan]]|Kenneth Preshon|[[Bump J|Terrence Boykin]]}}\n| extra1 = {{hlist|West|[[Francis and the Lights]]|[[Benny Blanco]]|Dean{{ref|b|[b]}}|[[Andy C]]{{ref|b|[b]}}|Aaron Lammer{{ref|b|[b]}}}}\n| length1 = 4:34\n\n| title2 = [[Yikes (song)|Yikes]]\n| writer2 = {{hlist|West|Dean|James Mbarack Achieng|[[Ayub Ogada]]|[[Drake (musician)|Aubrey Graham]]|Young|Mills|[[070 Shake|Danielle Balbuena]]|[[Pi'erre Bourne|Jordan Jenks]]|Asten Harris|Yusef|Preshon|Boykin|[[Pardison Fontaine|Jordan Thorpe]]}}\n| extra2 = {{hlist|West|Dean{{ref|a|[a]}}|[[Pi'erre Bourne]]{{ref|b|[b]}}|Apex Martin{{ref|b|[b]}}}} \n| length2 = 3:08\n\n| title3 = [[All Mine (Kanye West song)|All Mine]]\n| writer3 = {{h