-latest-album-ye-2400275 |archive-date=April 26, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* \"Yikes\" contains a sample from \"Kothbiro\", as performed by Black Savage.\n* \"Wouldn't Leave\" contains a sample from \"Baptizing Scene\", as performed by Reverend W.A. Donaldson.\n* \"No Mistakes\" contains a sample from \"Children (Get Together)\", as performed by Edwin Hawkins Singers; and \"Hey Young World\", as performed by [[Slick Rick]].\n* \"Ghost Town\" contain a sample from \"Take Me for a Little While\", as performed by The Royal Jesters; and \"Someday\", as performed by Shirley Ann Lee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/thepitch/6-takeaways-from-kanye-wests-new-album-ye/|title=6 Takeaways from Kanye West's New Album, ye|website=Pitchfork|last1=Kim|first1=Michelle|last2=Pearce|first2=Sheldon|date=June 1, 2018|accessdate=June 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143955/https://pitchfork.com/thepitch/6-takeaways-from-kanye-wests-new-album-ye/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Friedman|first1=Roger|url=http://www.showbiz411.com/2018/06/02/heres-the-main-sample-on-kanye-wests-new-album-by-the-royal-jesters|title=Here's are the Main Samples on Kanye West's New Album, by the Royal Jesters, by Shirley Ann Lee|date=June 3, 2018|publisher=Showbiz411|access-date=June 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140939/http://www.showbiz411.com/2018/06/02/heres-the-main-sample-on-kanye-wests-new-album-by-the-royal-jesters|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from Tidal.<ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n\n* [[Mike Dean (record producer)|Mike Dean]] \u2013 engineering, mixing\n* Mike Malchicoff \u2013 engineering\n* Zack Djurich \u2013 engineering\n* [[Andrew Dawson (record producer)|Andrew Dawson]] \u2013 engineering {{small|(tracks 2, 7)}}, programming {{small|(tracks 2, 7)}}\n* William J. Sullivan \u2013 engineering {{small|(track 5)}}\n* Noah Goldstein \u2013 recordin