"Vibe\">{{cite web |title=Here's Every Sample & Featured Artist on Kanye West's 'Ye' Album |url=https://www.vibe.com/2018/06/every-sample-featured-artist-on-kanye-wests-ye-album/ |website=Vibe |accessdate=June 3, 2018 |date=June 1, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612185037/https://www.vibe.com/2018/06/every-sample-featured-artist-on-kanye-wests-ye-album/ |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* The original version of \"I Thought About Killing You\" contains an uncredited sample from \"Fr3sh\", as performed by Kareem Lotfy.<ref name=\"Lotfy\">{{cite news |last1=Daly |first1=Rhian |title=Kanye West quietly makes change to latest album 'Ye' |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/kanye-west-quietly-makes-change-latest-album-ye-2400275 |website=NME |accessdate=April 2, 2020 |date=November 8, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190426094542/https://www.nme.com/news/music/kanye-west-quietly-makes-change-latest-album-ye-2400275 |archive-date=April 26, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* \"Yikes\" contains a sample from \"Kothbiro\", as performed by Black Savage.\n* \"Wouldn't Leave\" contains a sample from \"Baptizing Scene\", as performed by Reverend W.A. Donaldson.\n* \"No Mistakes\" contains a sample from \"Children (Get Together)\", as performed by Edwin Hawkins Singers; and \"Hey Young World\", as performed by [[Slick Rick]].\n* \"Ghost Town\" contain a sample from \"Take Me for a Little While\", as performed by The Royal Jesters; and \"Someday\", as performed by Shirley Ann Lee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/thepitch/6-takeaways-from-kanye-wests-new-album-ye/|title=6 Takeaways from Kanye West's New Album, ye|website=Pitchfork|last1=Kim|first1=Michelle|last2=Pearce|first2=Sheldon|date=June 1, 2018|accessdate=June 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143955/https://pitchfork.com/thepitch/6-takeaways-from-kanye-wests-new-album-ye/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Friedman|first1=Roger|url=http://www.showbiz411.com/2018/06/02/heres-the-main-sample-on-kanye-wests-new-album-by-the-royal-jesters|title=Here's are the Main Samples on Kanye West's New Album, by the Royal Jesters, by Shirley Ann Lee|date=June 3, 2018|publisher=Showbiz411|access-date=June 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140939/http://www.showbiz411.com/2018/06/02/heres-the-main-sample-on-kanye-wests-new-album-by-the-royal-jesters|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from Tidal.<ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n\n* [[Mike Dean (record producer)|Mike Dean]] \u2013 engineering, mixing\n* Mike Malchicoff \u2013 engineering\n* Zack Djurich \u2013 engineering\n* [[Andrew Dawson (record producer)|Andrew Dawson]] \u2013 engineering {{small|(tracks 2, 7)}}, programming {{small|(tracks 2, 7)}}\n* William J. Sullivan \u2013 engineering {{small|(track 5)}}\n* Noah Goldstein \u2013 recording engineering {{small|(tracks 2, 4)}}, engineering {{small|(track 6)}}\n* Mauricio Iragorri \u2013 recording engineering {{small|(track 6)}}\n* Sean Solymar \u2013 assistant recording engineering {{small|(tracks 1\u20135)}}\n* [[Jess Jackson (record producer)|Jess Jackson]] \u2013 mixing\n* Mike Snell \u2013 assistant remix engineering {{small|(track 7)}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|1|artist=Kanye West|album=Ye|rowheader=true|accessdate=June 9, 2018}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australian Urban Albums ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/urban-albums-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 40 Urban Albums|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=June 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613112511/https://www.ariacharts.com.au/chart